CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 15, 1960, pg. 2 reads: "13th Ward Was There - Among the crowd of 20,000 which greeted Senator John F. Kennedy at Gateway Center on Monday evening, was a large contingent from the hustling bustling 13th Ward. Their identification placards can be seen in photograph.  Many persons in the crowd had been waiting in the sun since 3 P.M. Senator Kennedy and his entourage did not reach the downtown area until some two hours later. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Kennedy -Johnson presidential campaign: Man, possibly David L. Lawrence, addressing crowd in front of the Pittsburgh Hilton Hotel, Downtown
